#: ../../../build_instructions/build.md:1
#: ../../../build_instructions/build.md:247
msgid "Building"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../build_instructions/build.md:3
msgid ""
"This page describes how to build and install VTK. It covers building for "
"development, on both Unix-type systems (Linux, HP-UX, Solaris, macOS), and "
"Windows. Note that Unix-like environments such as Cygwin and MinGW are not "
"officially supported. However, patches to fix problems with these platforms "
"will be considered for inclusion. It is recommended that users which require "
"VTK to work on these platforms to submit nightly testing results for them."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../build_instructions/build.md:10
msgid ""
"A full-featured build of VTK depends on several open source tools and "
"libraries such as Python, Qt, CGNS, HDF5, etc. Some of these are included in "
"the VTK source itself (e.g., HDF5), while others are expected to be present "
"on the machine on which VTK is being built (e.g., Python, Qt)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../build_instructions/build.md:15
msgid ""
"VTK supports all of the common generators supported by CMake. The Ninja, "
"Makefiles, and Visual Studio generators are the most well-tested however."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../build_instructions/build.md:18
msgid ""
"Note that VTK does not support in-source builds, so you must have a build "
"tree that is not the source tree."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../build_instructions/build.md:21
msgid "Obtaining the sources"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../build_instructions/build.md:23
msgid "There are two approaches:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../build_instructions/build.md:0
msgid "Release Download"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../build_instructions/build.md:29
msgid ""
"Download the source release `VTK-X.Y.Z.tar.gz` from https://vtk.org/"
"download/."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../build_instructions/build.md:30
msgid "Create a folder for VTK."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../build_instructions/build.md:31
msgid ""
"Extract the contents of the VTK folder in the downloaded archive to the "
"subfolder called `source`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../build_instructions/build.md:0
msgid "Git Clone"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../build_instructions/build.md:35
msgid ""
"To obtain VTK's sources locally, clone the VTK repository using [Git][git]."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../build_instructions/build.md:39
msgid ""
"Open `Git Bash` on Windows or a terminal on Linux and macOS and execute the "
"following:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../build_instructions/build.md:42
msgid ""
"mkdir -p ~/vtk\n"
"git clone --recursive https://gitlab.kitware.com/vtk/vtk.git ~/vtk/source\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../build_instructions/build.md:49
msgid ""
"To use the latest features being developed or to make changes and contribute "
"to VTK, download the source using **Git Clone**."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../build_instructions/build.md:52
msgid "Prerequisites"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../build_instructions/build.md:54
msgid ""
"VTK only requires a few packages in order to build in general, however "
"specific features may require additional packages to be provided to VTK's "
"build configuration."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../build_instructions/build.md:58
msgid "Required:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../build_instructions/build.md:60
msgid "[CMake][cmake]"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../build_instructions/build.md:61
msgid ""
"Version 3.12 or newer, however, the latest version is always recommended. If "
"the system package management utilities do not offer cmake or if the offered "
"version is too old Precompiled binaries available on [CMake's download page]"
"[cmake-download]."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../build_instructions/build.md:65
msgid "  <!-- Keep this section in sync with top-level README.md -->\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../build_instructions/build.md:66
msgid "Supported compiler"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../build_instructions/build.md:67
msgid "GCC 8.0 or newer"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../build_instructions/build.md:68
msgid "Clang 7.0 or newer"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../build_instructions/build.md:69
msgid "Apple Clang 11.0 (Xcode 11.3.1) or newer"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../build_instructions/build.md:70
msgid "Microsoft Visual Studio 2019 or newer"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../build_instructions/build.md:71
msgid "Intel 19.0 or newer"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../build_instructions/build.md:73
msgid "Optional Additions"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../build_instructions/build.md:75
msgid ""
"**ffmpeg** When the ability to write `.avi` files is desired, and writing "
"these files is not supported by the OS, VTK can use the ffmpeg library. This "
"is generally true for Unix-like operating systems. Source code for ffmpeg "
"can be obtained from [the website][ffmpeg]."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../build_instructions/build.md:81
msgid ""
"**MPI** To run VTK in parallel, an [MPI][mpi] implementation is required. If "
"an MPI implementation that exploits special interconnect hardware is "
"provided on your system, we suggest using it for optimal performance. "
"Otherwise, on Linux/Mac, we suggest either [OpenMPI][openmpi] or [MPICH]"
"[mpich]. On Windows, [Microsoft MPI][msmpi] is required."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../build_instructions/build.md:88
msgid ""
"**Python** In order to use scripting, [Python][python] is required. The "
"minimum supported version is **3.4**. The instructions are using the system "
"Python. On Ubuntu/Debian the required package is `python3-dev`. If you use a "
"different Python implementation or a virtual environment make sure the "
"environment you use is activated. On Ubuntu/Debian the required package for "
"creating virtual environments is `python3-venv`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../build_instructions/build.md:96
msgid ""
"**Qt5** VTK uses Qt as its GUI library (if the relevant modules are "
"enabled). Precompiled binaries are available on [Qt's website][qt-download]. "
"Note that on Windows, the compiler used for building VTK must match the "
"compiler version used to build Qt. Version **5.9** or newer is required."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../build_instructions/build.md:102
msgid ""
"**OSMesa** Off-screen Mesa can be used as a software-renderer for running "
"VTK on a server without hardware OpenGL acceleration. This is usually "
"available in system packages on Linux. For example, the `libosmesa6-dev` "
"package on Debian and Ubuntu. However, for older machines, building a newer "
"version of Mesa is likely necessary for bug fixes and support. Its source "
"and build instructions can be found on [its website][mesa]."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../build_instructions/build.md:121
msgid "Creating the Build Environment"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../build_instructions/build.md:0
msgid "Windows"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../build_instructions/build.md:128
#: ../../../build_instructions/build.md:164
msgid "Install CMake"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../build_instructions/build.md:130
msgid "Install [Visual Studio Community Edition][visual-studio]"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../build_instructions/build.md:132
msgid ""
"During installation select the \"desktop development with C++\" workload."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../build_instructions/build.md:134
msgid ""
"Use \"x64 Native Tools Command Prompt\" for the installed Visual Studio "
"version to configure with CMake and to build with ninja."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../build_instructions/build.md:137
msgid ""
"Get [ninja][ninja]. Unzip the binary and put it in `PATH`. Note that newer "
"Visual Studio releases come with a version of `ninja` already and should "
"already exist in `PATH` within the command prompt."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../build_instructions/build.md:0
msgid "Linux (Ubuntu/Debian)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../build_instructions/build.md:148
msgid "Install the following packages:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../build_instructions/build.md:150
msgid ""
"$ sudo apt install \\\n"
"build-essential \\\n"
"cmake \\\n"
"cmake-curses-gui \\\n"
"mesa-common-dev \\\n"
"mesa-utils \\\n"
"freeglut3-dev \\\n"
"ninja-build\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../build_instructions/build.md:0
msgid "macOS"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../build_instructions/build.md:166
msgid "Install XCode"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../build_instructions/build.md:168
msgid "Ensure XCode command line tools are installed:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../build_instructions/build.md:170
msgid "xcode-select --install\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../build_instructions/build.md:177
msgid ""
"`ninja` is a more efficient alternative to `Makefiles` or Visual Studio "
"solution files. The speed increase is the most noticeable when doing "
"incremental build. `ninja` version 1.10.1 or higher is required."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../build_instructions/build.md:182
msgid "Configure"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../build_instructions/build.md:184
msgid ""
"In order to build, CMake requires two steps, configure and build. VTK itself "
"does not support what are known as in-source builds, so the first step is to "
"create a build directory."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../build_instructions/build.md:0
msgid "Windows (Ninja)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../build_instructions/build.md:193
msgid ""
"Open \"x64 Native Tools Command Prompt\" for the installed Visual Studio:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../build_instructions/build.md:195
msgid "ccmake -GNinja -S %HOMEPATH%\\vtk\\source -B %HOMEPATH%\\vtk\\build\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../build_instructions/build.md:199
msgid ""
"Note that CMake GUI must also be launched from the \"Native Tools Command "
"Prompt\"."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../build_instructions/build.md:0
msgid "Windows (Visual Studio)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../build_instructions/build.md:205
msgid "Use CMake to generate a Visual Studio solution file (`.sln`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../build_instructions/build.md:207
msgid ""
"Open CMake GUI, either by typing `cmake-gui` on the command prompt or from "
"the start-menu."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../build_instructions/build.md:208
msgid "Enter the source and build directories"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../build_instructions/build.md:209
msgid "Click `[Configure]`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../build_instructions/build.md:210
msgid ""
"You will now get a selection screen in which you can specify your "
"\"generator\". Select the one you need."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../build_instructions/build.md:211
msgid ""
"We are now presented with a few options that can be turned on or off as "
"desired."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../build_instructions/build.md:212
msgid "Click `[Configure]` to apply the changes."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../build_instructions/build.md:213
msgid "Click `[Generate]`. This will populate the \"build\" sub-folder."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../build_instructions/build.md:214
msgid ""
"Finally, click `[Open Project]` to open the generated solution in Visual "
"Studio."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../build_instructions/build.md:0
msgid "Linux/macOS"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../build_instructions/build.md:220
msgid ""
"mkdir -p ~/vtk/build\n"
"cd ~/vtk/build\n"
"ccmake -GNinja ../path/to/vtk/source\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../build_instructions/build.md:226
msgid ""
"The parameter `-GNinja` may be skipped to use the default generator (e.g "
"`Unix Makefiles`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../build_instructions/build.md:230
msgid "**Missing dependencies**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../build_instructions/build.md:233
msgid ""
"CMake may not find all dependencies automatically in all cases. The steps "
"needed to find any given package depends on the package itself."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../build_instructions/build.md:236
msgid ""
"For general assistance, please see the documentation for [`find_package`'s "
"search procedure][cmake-find_package-search] and [the relevant Find module]"
"[cmake-modules-find] (as available)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../build_instructions/build.md:244
msgid ""
"Different features can be enabled/disabled by setting the [Build Settings]"
"(build_settings.md) during the configure stage, one can even use presets "
"such as `default`, `mini` or `dev` with the `--preset=default` cmake "
"argument."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../build_instructions/build.md:249
msgid "To build VTK:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../build_instructions/build.md:256
msgid "cmake --build %HOMEPATH%\\vtk\\build --config Release\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../build_instructions/build.md:263
msgid "Open the generated solution file."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../build_instructions/build.md:265
msgid "Set the configuration to \"Release\""
msgstr ""

#: ../../../build_instructions/build.md:267
msgid "On the menu bar, choose `Build`, and then choose `Build Solution`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../build_instructions/build.md:272
msgid "cmake --build ~/vtk/build\n"
msgstr ""
